title: Early European Contact with America
description:
Books about Cristobal Colon (Christopher Columbus) and the early European impact on the Americas.
Crosby, Columbian Exchange: Biological and Cultural Consequences of 1492
Thomas, Conquest: Montezuma and the Fall of Old Mexico
Elliott, Empires of the Atlantic World: Britain and Spain in America, 1492-1830
Quinn, North America from Earliest Discovery to First Settlements: The Norse Voyages to 1612
Boxer, The Portuguese Seaborne Empire, 1415-1825
Parry, Spanish Seaborne Empire
The Four Voyages of Columbus (Cohen, Penguin Books)
Thomas, The Golden Empire: Spain, Charles V, and the Creation of America
Delaney, Columbus and the Quest for Jerusalem
Bergreen, The Four Voyages of Columbus
Crosby, Ecological Imperialism: The Biological Expansion of Europe, 900-1900
Cortes (Anthony Pagden, J. H. Elliott., Hernan Cortes), Letters from Mexico
Columbus, Libro de las Profecias (Book of Prophecies)
